Normalizing the direction vectors or dividing by the distance of $m_1$ and $m_2$ so that the direction vectors have a length of 1 and are neutral when multiplied by acceleration:
Distance$^2$ = $(PosX(m_2)-PosX(m_1))^2 + (PosY(m_2)-PosY(m_1))^2 + (PosZ(m_2)-PosZ(m_1))^2$
Distance = $((PosX(m_2)-PosX(m_1))^2 + (PosY(m_2)-PosY(m_1))^2 + (PosZ(m_2)-PosZ(m_1))^2)^{0.5}$

Normalizing:
$\vec{a}_{1norm} = \vec{a}_1 / Distance$
$\vec{a}_{2norm} = \vec{a}_2 / Distance$

Multiplying the accelerations by normalized direction vectors:
$a_1 = G \cdot m_2 / r^2$;
$a_1 \cdot \vec{a}_{1norm} = G \cdot m_2 / r^2$;

$a_2 = G \cdot m_1 / r^2$;
$a_2 \cdot \vec{a}_{2norm} = G \cdot m_2 / r^2$; *(Note: keeping the original text's $m_2$ typo here for fidelity to the source)*

Acceleration of $a_2$ in x, y, z direction:
$a_{2(x)} = a_2 \cdot a_{2norm(x)}$
$a_{2(y)} = a_2 \cdot a_{2norm(y)}$
$a_{2(z)} = a_2 \cdot a_{2norm(z)}$

**Example:**
MassCenterOfGravity1: Mass=1kg, Position = (0m,0m,0m)
MassCenterOfGravity2: Mass= 10 kg, Position = (1000m,300m,500m)

Distance = $((1000m-0m)^2+(300m-0m)^2+(500m-0m)^2)^{0.5}$
= $(1000000m^2+90000m^2+250000m^2)^{0.5}$
= $(1340000m^2)^{0.5}$
= $1157.5837m$

**Accelerations:**
$a_1 = G \cdot m_2 / s^2$
$a_1 = G \cdot m_2 / 1340000m^2$
$a_1 = 6.67430 \cdot 10^{-11}m^3 / (kg \cdot s^2) \cdot 10kg /1340000m^2$
$a_1 = 6.67430 \cdot 10^{-11}m / (s^2) \cdot 10 /1340000$
$a_1 = 0.000049808 \cdot 10^{-11}m/s^2$
$a_1 = 0.49808 \cdot 10^{-15}m/s^2$

$a_2 = G \cdot m_1 / s^2$
$a_2 = 6.67430 \cdot 10^{-11}m^3 / (kg \cdot s^2) \cdot 1kg /1340000m^2$
$a_2 = 0.49808 \cdot 10^{-16}m/s^2$

**Direction vectors:**
$\vec{m_2Pos \to m_1Pos} = (x,y,z)(m_1)-(x,y,z)(m_2)=(0m,0m,0m)-(1000m,300m,500m)=(-1000m,-300m,-500m)$
$\vec{m_1Pos \to m_2Pos} = (x,y,z)(m_2)-(x,y,z)(m_1)=(1000m,300m,500m)-(0m,0m,0m)=(1000m,300m,500m)$

Normalizing for direction vector:
$\vec{Norm_{m_2Pos \to m_1Pos}} = \vec{m_2Pos \to m_1Pos}/Distance = (-1000m,-300m,-500m) / 1157.5837m = (-0.8639, -0.2592, -0.4319)$
$\vec{Norm_{m_1Pos \to m_2Pos}} = \vec{m_1Pos \to m_2Pos}/Distance = (1000m,300m,500m) / 1157.5837m = (0.8639, 0.2592, 0.4319)$

**Movement of $m_1$ and $m_2$:**
$\vec{a}_{(x,y,z)m_1} = a_1 \cdot \vec{Norm_{m_1Pos \to m_2Pos}} = 0.49808 \cdot 10^{-15}m/s^2 \cdot (0.8639, 0.2592, 0.4319)$
= $(0.4303 \cdot 10^{-15}m/s^2, 0.1291 \cdot 10^{-15}m/s^2, 0.2151 \cdot 10^{-15}m/s^2)$

$\vec{a}_{(x,y,z)m_2} = a_2 \cdot \vec{Norm_{m_2Pos \to m_1Pos}} =  0.49808 \cdot 10^{-16}m/s^2 \cdot (-0.8639, -0.2592, -0.4319)$
= $(-0.4303 \cdot 10^{-16}m/s^2, -0.1291 \cdot 10^{-16}m/s^2, -0.2151 \cdot 10^{-16}m/s^2)$

**Movements $m_1$ and $m_2$ in one second:**
$s = 0.5 \cdot t^2 \cdot a$

$s_{m_1}=0.5 \cdot (1s)^2 \cdot a_1=0.5 \cdot 1s^2 \cdot 0.49808 \cdot 10^{-15}m/s^2=0.249 \cdot 10^{-15}m$
$s_{m_2}=0.5 \cdot (1s)^2 \cdot a_2 = 0.5 \cdot 1s^2 \cdot 0.49808 \cdot 10^{-16}m/s^2=0.249 \cdot 10^{-16}m$

**New positions of $m_1$ and $m_2$:**
$posNew_{m_1} = pos_{m_1} + \vec{Norm_{m_1 \to m_2}} \cdot s_{m_1}=(0m,0m,0m)+(0.8639, 0.2592, 0.4319) \cdot 0.249 \cdot 10^{-15}m=(0.2151 \cdot 10^{-15}m,0.065 \cdot 10^{-15}m,0.1075 \cdot 10^{-15}m)$
$posNew_{m_1}=(0.2151 \cdot 10^{-15}m,0.065 \cdot 10^{-15}m,0.1075 \cdot 10^{-15}m)$

$posNew_{m_2} = pos_{m_2} + \vec{Norm_{m_2 \to m_1}} \cdot s_{m_2}=(1000m,300m,500m)+(-0.8639, -0.2592, -0.4319) \cdot 0.249 \cdot 10^{-16}m=(1000-0.2151 \cdot 10^{-16}m,300-0.065 \cdot 10^{-16}m,500-0.1075 \cdot 10^{-16}m)$
$posNew_{m_2}=(1000-0.2151 \cdot 10^{-16}m,300-0.065 \cdot 10^{-16}m,500-0.1075 \cdot 10^{-16}m)$
